      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "<p>Addition of HCl to 1-methoxycyclohexene yields 1-chloro-1-methoxycyclohexane as a sole product. Use resonance structures to explain why none of the other regioisomer is formed.</p>\n<img class=\"scaled-down-30\" src=\"https://exercises.openstax.org/rails/active_storage/blobs/proxy/eyJfcmFpbHMiOnsibWVzc2FnZSI6IkJBaHBBZ1FWIiwiZXhwIjpudWxsLCJwdXIiOiJibG9iX2lkIn19--acafabb8acf5e4b9e9a8265241da30a2db9c5fb4/OChem_14_EC_028.jpg\" alt=\"A cyclohexene with a double bond between C1-C2 and a methoxy group at C1 reacts with hydrogen chloride to form a cyclohexane ring, in which C 1 is bonded to a methoxy group and a chlorine atom.\">",
